Arrow Funcitons:
----------------
	*ES6 version
	*more readable and more structure
	*Annonuymous functions(lambda Functions)
	*without FUNCTION NAME BUT THEY ARE ASSIGNED to a variable.
	-->EX:
		1)Arrow functions without parameters;
			let c=()=>{
				console.log("hi name")
			}
			c()
		2)Arrow functions with the parameters
			let A=(x,y)=>{
				console.log(x+y)
			}
			A(10,20)
			A(5,10)

        3)Arrow function with one argument.Without using paranthesis
            let greet=x=>console.log(x);
            greet('hello name')


-->Ternary Operator: The conditional (ternary) operator is the only JavaScript operator
                     that takes three operands: a condition followed by a question mark ( ? ),
                     then an expression to execute if the condition is truthy followed by a colon ( : ),
                     and finally the expression to execute if the condition is falsy.
            Syntax--> (condition)? E1:E2
            EX:->let age=18;
                let welcome=(age<18)?       //here if the condition is true then the first statement will be printed orelse the next statemnt will be printed same as of if else conditions
                ()=>console.log("hi")
                ()=>console.log("hello")
                welcome()

        Synchronous and Asyncronous functions:->ASynchronous[A step by step process a multi step processes]


        Note:->setTimeout()-->built in function

                EX: console.log("hi kiran")          //here first the hi kiran will be executed the bye kiran will be executed because the Asyncronousfunction is defined i.e the time to load is for the i am waiting is 5000 so before it gets load the last statement will be executed.
                    setTimeout(()=>{
                    console.log("I am waiting here")   
                    5000;
                    })
                    console.log("bye kiran")


---->JavaScript Callbacks:
            It is a function that is passed argument to another function;
                EX: function greet(name, callback){
                            console.log(`hello,${name}!`)
                            callback();     // this si the callback function after greeting
                            }
                            fucntion sayGoodbye(){
                            console.log("Good Bye")
                            }



 </script> -->
